doc_summary_long: Popular cloud storage firm Dropbox has been hacked, with over 68 million users' email addresses and passwords leaking on to the internet. The attack took place during 2012. At the time Dropbox reported a collection of user's email addresses had been stolen. It did not report that passwords had been stolen as well. The dump of passwords came to light when the database was picked up by security notification service Leakbase, which sent it to Motherboard.
doc_summary_short: Popular cloud storage firm Dropbox has been hacked, with over 68 million users' email addresses and passwords leaking on to the internet.
doc_title: Dropbox hack leads to leaking of 68 million user passwords on the internet.
